Change the existing Apiserver manifest argument to: --etcd-servers=this-is-very-wrong

1. take backup of /etc/manifests/kubernetes/kube-apiserver.yaml
2. make the change
3. watch crictl ps
4. k -n kube-system get pod - we are looking for api-server
5. cat /var/log/pods/kube-system_kube-apiserver-controlplane_e24b....
> Err: connection error: desc = "transport: Error while dialing dial tcp: address this-is-very-wrong: missing port in address". Reconnecting...
6. crictl ps - find the api server pod
7. crictl logs f669a6f3afda2
> Error while dialing dial tcp: address this-is-very-wrong: missing port in address. Reconnecting...
8. journalctl | grep apiserver # nothing specific
cat /var/log/syslog | grep apiserver # nothing specific
9. restore from backup

logs to check:
1. /var/log/pods
2. /var/log/containers
3. crictl ps + crictl logs
4. docker ps + docker logs (in case when Docker is used)
5. kubelet logs: /var/log/syslog or journalctl